 In every case, we need to write down the types in the form of a simple
 (non-curried) function, such as 
\begin_inset Formula $P\rightarrow Q$
\end_inset

, where 
\begin_inset Formula $P$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $Q$
\end_inset

