\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
T & =P+A\times(P+A\times(P+...))\\
 & =P+A\times P+A\times A\times P+A\times A\times A\times P+...\\
 & =P\times(\bbnum 1+A+A\times A+A\times A\times A+...)\\
 & =P\times\text{List}^{A}\quad.
\end{align*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
The infinite type expressions are suggestive but not rigorous.
 To prove that 
\begin_inset Formula $T\triangleq P\times\text{List}^{A}$
\end_inset

 is a fixpoint of the type equation 
\begin_inset Formula $T\cong G^{T}$
\end_inset

