\begin_inset Formula $T$
\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset Formula $P+A\times T$
\end_inset

.
 For that, we just need to implement two functions, 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

fix
\end_layout

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

unfix
\end_layout

\end_inset

, that are inverses of each other: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{align*}
 & \text{fix}:P\times\text{List}^{A}\rightarrow P+A\times(P\times\text{List}^{A})\quad,\\
 & \text{unfix}:P+A\times(P\times\text{List}^{A})\rightarrow P\times\text{List}^{A}\quad,\\
 & \text{fix}\bef\text{unfix}=\text{id}\quad,\quad\quad\text{unfix}\bef\text{fix}=\text{id}\quad.
\end{align*}

\end_inset

We write the code for 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

fix
\end_layout

\end_inset

 and 
\begin_inset listings
inline true
status open

\begin_layout Plain Layout

unfix
\end_layout

\end_inset

 in matrix form, expanding the disjunctive type as 
\begin_inset Formula $P\times\text{List}^{A}\cong P\times(\bbnum 1+A\times\text{List}^{A})$
\end_inset

